data.name: Activity_Delete_Description
data.value: Removes a specified file from an FTP server. This activity only works if it is placed inside a With FTP Session scope activity.

data.name: Activity_Delete_Property_RemotePath_Description
data.value: The path of the file that is to be removed from the FTP server.

data.name: Activity_DirectoryExists_Description
data.value: Checks whether a certain directory exists on an FTP server. This activity only works if it is placed inside a With FTP Session scope activity.

data.name: Activity_DirectoryExists_Property_Exists_Description
data.value: A boolean variable that states whether the indicated directory was found or not.

data.name: Activity_DirectoryExists_Property_RemotePath_Description
data.value: The path of the FTP directory in which to check whether the indicated directory exists.

data.name: Activity_EnumerateObjects_Description
data.value: Generates a DataTable variable that contains a list comprising the files found at the specified FTP server path. Subfolders can also be included in the search by checking the Includes subfolders box. This activity only works if it is placed inside a With FTP Session scope activity.

data.name: Activity_EnumerateObjects_Property_Files_Description
data.value: A collection of files that have been found on the FTP server.

data.name: Activity_EnumerateObjects_Property_Recursive_Description
data.value: If this check box is selected, the subfolders are also included in the enumeration of the files on the FTP server.

data.name: Activity_EnumerateObjects_Property_RemotePath_Description
data.value: The path of the directory on the FTP server whose files are to be enumerated.

data.name: Activity_FileExists_Description
data.value: Checks whether a certain file exists in the specified FTP directory. This activity only works if it is placed inside a With FTP Session scope activity.

data.name: Activity_FileExists_Property_Exists_Description
data.value: A boolean variable that states whether the indicated file was found or not.

data.name: Activity_FileExists_Property_RemotePath_Description
data.value: The path of the FTP directory in which to check whether the indicated file exists.

data.name: Activity_UploadFiles_Description
data.value: Uploads a file to an FTP server. This activity only works if it is placed inside a With FTP Session scope activity.

data.name: Activity_UploadFiles_Property_Create_Description
data.value: If this box is checked, the folder path will be created on the FTP server in case it does not already exist.

data.name: Activity_UploadFiles_Property_LocalPath_Description
data.value: The local path of the files that are to be uploaded.

data.name: Activity_UploadFiles_Property_Overwrite_Description
data.value: If this box is checked, the files will be overwritten on the FTP server if they're already stored there.

data.name: Activity_UploadFiles_Property_Recursive_Description
data.value: If this box is checked, the folders will be uploaded with their respective subfolders.

data.name: Activity_UploadFiles_Property_RemotePath_Description
data.value: The path on the FTP server where the file is to be uploaded.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Description
data.value: A container which handles the connection to the FTP server and provides a scope for all the FTP activities.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_AcceptAllCertificates_Description
data.value: If this box is checked, all certificates will be accepted, including the ones that are expired or not verified.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_ClientCertificatePassword_Description
data.value: The password for the client certificate.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_ClientCertificatePath_Description
data.value: The path to the certificate used to verify the identity of the client.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_ContinueOnError_Description
data.value: Specifies if the automation should continue even when the activity throws an error.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_FtpsMode_Description
data.value: Switches to the FTPS protocol. Choose one of the two available options: Explicit or Implicit.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_Host_Description
data.value: The URL of the FTP server that you want to connect to.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_Password_Description
data.value: The password that will be used to connect to the FTP server.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_Port_Description
data.value: The port of the FTP server that you want to connect to.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_SslProtocols_Description
data.value: Select the SSL protocol to be used for the FTPS connection

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_UseAnonymousLogin_Description
data.value: When this box is checked, the username and password fields are ignored, and a standard anonymous user is used instead.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_Username_Description
data.value: The username that will be used to connect to the FTP server.

data.name: Activity_WithFtpSession_Property_UseSftp_Description
data.value: Check this box if you want to use the SFTP transfer protocol.

data.name: Activity_DownloadFiles_Description
data.value: Downloads the specified files from an FTP server to the specified local folder. This activity only works if it is placed inside a With FTP Session scope activity.

data.name: Activity_DownloadFiles_Property_Create_Description
data.value: If this box is checked, the folder path will be created locally in case it does not already exist.

data.name: Activity_DownloadFiles_Property_LocalPath_Description
data.value: The local path for the files that are to be downloaded.

data.name: Activity_DownloadFiles_Property_Overwrite_Description
data.value: If this box is checked, the files will be overwritten locally if they're already stored there.

data.name: Activity_DownloadFiles_Property_Recursive_Description
data.value: If this box is checked, the folders will be downloaded with their respective subfolders.

data.name: Activity_DownloadFiles_Property_RemotePath_Description
data.value: The path of the files on the FTP server that are to be downloaded.

data.name: Activity_MoveItem_Description
data.value: Moves an item on an FTP server to a different remote path. This activity only works if it is placed inside a With FTP

data.name: Activity_MoveItem_Property_ContinueOnError_Description
data.value: Specifies if the automation should continue even when the activity throws an error.

data.name: Activity_MoveItem_Property_NewPath_Description
data.value: The remote path on the FTP server where the file will be moved.

data.name: Activity_MoveItem_Property_Overwrite_Description
data.value: If this box is checked, the files will be overwritten in the new remote directory if they're already stored there.

data.name: Activity_MoveItem_Property_RemotePath_Description
data.value: The remote path on the FTP server where the file is currently located.
